  "text": "The butterfly processor, shown in Fig. 3 , is designed with a view to supporting one-cycle execution of decimation-in-frequency FFT operations. The proposed processor has five special instructions for execution of six basic butterfly operations in FFT algorithms, such as Cooley-Tukey radix-2/4 [CITATION_1] , recursive-radix [CITATION_2] , radix- [CITATION_3] , split-radix [CITATION_4] , and others. All basic FFT operations except the decimation-in-time butterfly operation can be executed in one clock cycle. The twiddle factors are supplied from the built-in cos/sin ROM, which stores 1024 sinusoidal wave samples (1/8 of a period) and can support FFT computation with up to 8192 points. ",
